cs.CC, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.DM

The paper presents a pseudorandom generator for branching programs, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The use of Fourier analysis suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing. The paper also involves the analysis of data structures (cs.DS) and combinatorics (cs.DM) related to branching programs. Finally, the topic of pseudorandomness is often studied in cryptography (cs.CR).
